New Records: Jacob Bethell's 50 was his first international fifty
Brydon Carse achieved a shock maiden professional five-wicket haul
Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone scored 87 off 47 balls, including five sixes and six fours
Livingstone and Bethell shared a 90-run partnership off 47 balls
Adil Rashid steered to backward point for the single England needed for a three-wicket win with six balls to spare
Brydon Carse took a couple of wickets and impressed with his speed, breaching 90 mph (145 kph)
Jake Fraser-McGurk scored his first international fifty
Sean Abbott took two wickets in three balls
Miscellaneous Highlights: Livingstone, in his 50th T20, took 2-16 from three overs
Brydon Carse returned to cricket after a three-month ban for breaching betting regulations
The series winner will be decided on Sunday (September 15, 2024) at Old Trafford
